ith line numbering and optional offset/limit\n   - Write files\n   - Edit files by replacing specific strings (with safety checks)\n   - Glob pattern matching for file discovery\n   - Grep functionality for searching across files\n\n2. **System Commands**: \n   - Execute bash commands with 30-second timeout protection\n\n3. **AI Integration**: \n   - Connects to OpenRouter-compatible APIs (currently configured for Alibaba's DashScope/Qwen3)\n   - Uses function calling to let the AI use the available tools\n   - Maintains conversation history with tool usage context\n\n4. **Interactive CLI**: \n   - Real-time chat interface with colored output\n   - Command shortcuts (`/q` to quit, `/c` to clear conversation, `/stats` for usage statistics)\n   - Automatic logging of all interactions to `actions.log` and API responses to `api_responses.log`\n\n### **How It Works:**\n\nThe assistant operates in an **agentic loop**:\n1. User provides a coding task or question\n2. AI analyzes the request and decides which tools to use\n3. Tools execute (file operations, system commands, etc.)\n4. Results are fed back to the AI for further reasoning\n5. Process repeats until the task is complete or user intervention is needed\n\n### **Current Configuration:**\n- Uses **Qwen3-Max** model via Alibaba's DashScope API\n- Designed for concise, coding-focused assistance\n- Includes safety features like timeout protection and edit validation\n\nThis is essentially a **local development assistant** that can help with code navigation, file manipulation, and general programming tasks by combining AI reasoning with direct filesystem access."},{"role":"user","content":"\\stats"},{"role":"assistant","content":"I notice you're asking for stats, but the `\\stats` command is meant to be used within the running nanocode assistant application. Since we're not currently running the interactive CLI, I can't execute that command directly.\n\nHowever, I can check if there are any existing stats logs in the rep