,{"role":"tool","tool_call_id":"call_5ffee33c9b364f31a18d801f","content":"   1| import { readdir, stat, appendFile } from \"node:fs/promises\";\n   2| import { join } from \"node:path\";\n   3| import { z } from \"zod\";\n   4| \n   5| type ToolDef = {\n   6|     description: string;\n   7|     params: Record<string, string>;\n   8|     handler: (args: any) => Promise<any>;\n   9| };\n  10| \n  11| const toolsDef: Record<string, ToolDef> = {\n  12|     read: {\n  13|         description: \"read a file with optional offset and limit\",\n  14|         params: {\n  15|             path: \"string\",\n  16|             offset: \"number?\",\n  17|             limit: \"number?\"\n  18|         },\n  19|         handler: async (args: { path: string, offset?: number, limit?: number }) => {\n  20|             const { path } = args;\n  21|             const offset = args.offset ?? 0;\n  22|             const limit = args.limit;\n  23| \n  24|             const content = await Bun.file(path).text();\n  25|             const lines = content.split(\"\\n\");\n  26| \n  27|             const end = limit ? offset + limit : lines.length;\n  28|             const selected = lines.slice(offset, end);\n  29| \n  30|             return selected.map((line, idx) => {\n  31|                 const lineNum = (offset + idx + 1).toString().padStart(4, \" \");\n  32|                 return `${lineNum}| ${line}`;\n  33|             }).join(\"\\n\");\n  34|         }\n  35|     },\n  36|     write: {\n  37|         description: \"write a file\",\n  38|         params: {\n  39|             path: \"string\",\n  40|             content: \"string\"\n  41|         },\n  42|         handler: async (args: { path: string, content: string }) => {\n  43|             await Bun.write(args.path, args.content);\n  44|             return \"ok\";\n  45|         }\n  46|     },\n  47|     edit: {\n  48|         description: \"edit a file by replacing a string\",\n  49|         params: {\n  50|             path: \"string\",\n  51|             old: \"string\",\n  52|             new: \"string\",\n  53|             all: \"boolean?\"\n  54|         },\n  55|         handler: async (args: { path: string, old: string, new: string, all?: boolean }) => {\n  56|             const path = args.path;\n  57|             const oldContent = args.old;\n  58|             const newContent = args.new;\n  59|             const all = args.all ?? false;\n  60| \n  61|             const file = Bun.file(path);\n  62|             const text = await file.text();\n  63| \n  64|             if (!text.includes(oldContent)) {\n  65|                 return \"error: old_string not found\";\n  66|             }\n  67| \n  68|             const count = text.split(oldContent).length - 1;\n  69|             if (!all && count > 1) {\n  70|                 return `error: old_string appears ${count} times, must be unique (use all=true)`;\n  71|             }\n  72| \n  73|             const replacement = all\n  74|                 ? text.replaceAll(oldContent, newContent)\n  75|                 : text.replace(oldContent, newContent);\n  76| \n  77|             await Bun.write(path, replacement);\n  78|             return \"ok\";\n  79|         }\n  80|     },\n  81|     glob: {\n  82|         description: \"glob a directory\",\n  83|         params: {\n  84|             path: \"string?\",\n  85|             pat: \"string\"\n  86|         },\n  87|         handler: async (args: { path?: string, pat: string }) => {\n  88|             const dir = args.path || \".\";\n  89|             const pattern = args.pat;\n  90| \n  91|             const globPattern = join(dir, pattern);\n  92|             const glob = new Bun.Glob(globPattern);\n  93| \n  94|             const files: { path: string, mtime: number }[] = [];\n  95| \n  96|             for await (const file of glob.scan({ cwd: \".\" })) {\n  97|                 try {\n  98|                     const stats = await stat(file);\n  99|                     if (stats.isFile()) {\n 100|                         files.push({ path: file, mtime: stats.mtimeMs });\n 101|                     }\n 102|                 } catch (e) {\n 103|                     // ignore\n 104|                 }\n 105|             }\n 106| \n 107|             files.sort((a, b) => b.mtime - a.mtime);\n 108| \n 109|             return files.map(f => f.path).join(\"\\n\") || \"none\";\n 110|         }\n 111|     },\n 112|     grep: {\n 113|         description: \"grep files in a directory\",\n 114|         params: {\n 115|             path: \"string?\",\n 116|             pat: \"string\"\n 117|         },\n 118|         handler: async (args: { path?: string, pat: string }) => {\n 119|             const pattern = args.pat;\n 120|             const regex = new RegExp(pattern);\n 121|             const hits: string[] = [];\n 122|             const searchDir = args.path || \".\";\n 123|             const glob = new Bun.Glob(\"**/*\");\n 124| \n 125|             for await (const file of glob.scan({ cwd: searchDir })) {\n 126|                 try {\n 127|                     const fullPath = join(searchDir, file);\n 128|                     const stats = await stat(fullPath);\n 129|                     if (!stats.isFile()) continue;\n 130| \n 131|                     const content = await Bun.file(fullPath).text();\n 132|                     const lines = content.split(\"\\n\");\n 133| \n 134|                     for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {\n 135|                         if (regex.test(lines[i])) {\n 136|                             hits.push(`${fullPath}:${i + 1}:${lines[i].trimEnd()}`);\n 137|                         }\n 138|                     }\n 139|                     if (hits.length >= 50) break;\n 140|                 } catch (e) {\n 141|                     // ignore\n 142|                 }\n 143|             }\n 144| \n 145|             return hits.slice(0, 50).join(\"\\n\") || \"none\";\n 146|         }\n 147|     },\n 148|     bash: {\n 149|         description: \"run a bash command with timeout\",\n 150|         params: {\n 151|             cmd: \"string\"\n 152|         },\n 153|         handler: async (args: { cmd: string }) => {\n 154|             const command = args.cmd;\n 155|             const proc = Bun.spawn([\"bash\", \"-c\", command], {\n 156|                 stdout: \"pipe\",\n 157|                 stderr: \"pipe\",\n 158|             });\n 159| \n 160|             const timeoutSignal = AbortSignal.timeout(30000);\n 161|             let output = \"\";\n 162|             let timer: ReturnType<typeof setTimeout> | null = null;\n 163| \n 164|             try {\n 165|                 const exitPromise = proc.exited;\n 166|                 const timeoutPromise = new Promise<void>((_, reject) => {\n 167|                     timer = setTimeout(() => {\n 168|                         proc.kill();\n 169|                         reject(new Error(\"Timeout\"));\n 170|                     }, 30000);\n 171|                 });\n 172| \n 173|                 const readStream = async (reader: ReadableStreamDefaultReader<Uint8Array>) => {\n 174|                     try {\n 175|                         while (true) {\n 176|                             const { done, value } = await reader.read();\n 177|                             if (done) break;\n 178|                             const chunk = new TextDecoder().decode(value);\n 179|                             output += chunk;\n 180|                         }\n 181|                     } finally {\n 182|                         reader.releaseLock();\n 183|                     }\n 184|                 };\n 185| \n 186|                 await Promise.all([\n 187|                     readStream(proc.stdout.getReader()),\n 188|                     readStream(proc.stderr.getReader()),\n 189|                     Promise.race([exitPromise, timeoutPromise])\n 190|                 ]);\n 191| \n 192|             } catch (e) {\n 193|                 output += \"\\n(timed out after 30s)\";\n 194|             } finally {\n 195|                 if (timer) clearTimeout(timer);\n 196|             }\n 197| \n 198|             return output.trim() || \"(empty)\";\n 199|         }\n 200|     },\n 201| \n 202| };\n 203| \n 204| function mapTypeToZod(typeStr: string) {\n 205|     const isOptional = typeStr.endsWith(\"?\");\n 206|     const baseType = typeStr.replace(\"?\", \"\");\n 207| \n 208|     let schema: z.ZodType<any>;\n 209|     switch (baseType) {\n 210|         case \"string\": schema = z.string(); break;\n 211|         case \"number\": schema = z.number(); break;\n 212|         case \"boolean\": schema = z.boolean(); break;\n 213|         default: schema = z.any();\n 214|     }\n 215| \n 216|     if (isOptional) {\n 217|         schema = schema.optional();\n 218|     }\n 219|     return schema;\n 220| }\n 221| \n 222| const toolSchemas = Object.entries(toolsDef).reduce((acc, [name, def]) => {\n 223|     const shape: Record<string, z.ZodType<any>> = {};\n 224|     for (const [key, type] of Object.entries(def.params)) {\n 225|         shape[key] = mapTypeToZod(type);\n 226|     }\n 227|     acc[name] = z.object(shape);\n 228|     return acc;\n 229| }, {} as Record<string, z.ZodObject<any>>);\n 230| \n 231| export async function runTool(name: string, args: any) {\n 232|     const def = toolsDef[name];\n 233|     if (!def) {\n 234|         throw new Error(`Tool not found: ${name}`);\n 235|     }\n 236| \n 237|     const schema = toolSchemas[name];\n 238|     const validatedArgs = schema.parse(args);\n 239|     return def.handler(validatedArgs);\n 240| }\n 241| \n 242| export function makeSchema() {\n 243|     const result = [];\n 244|     for (const [name, def] of Object.entries(toolsDef)) {\n 245|         const properties: Record<string, { type: string }> = {};\n 246|         const required: string[] = [];\n 247| \n 248|         for (const [paramName, paramType] of Object.entries(def.params)) {\n 249|             const isOptional = paramType.endsWith(\"?\");\n 250|             const baseType = paramType.replace(\"?\", \"\");\n 251| \n 252|             // Map TypeScript types to JSON schema types\n 253|             const jsonType = baseType === \"number\" ? \"integer\" : baseType;\n 254| \n 255|             properties[paramName] = { type: jsonType };\n 256|             if (!isOptional) {\n 257|                 required.push(paramName);\n 258|             }\n 259|         }\n 260| \n 261|         result.push({\n 262|             name,\n 263|             description: def.description,\n 264|             input_schema: {\n 265|                 type: \"object\",\n 266|                 properties,\n 267|                 required\n 268|             }\n 269|         });\n 270|     }\n 271|     return result;\n 272| }\n 273| \n 274| \n 275| // --- Agentic Loop Implementation ---\n 276| \n 277| import { createInterface } from \"node:readline/promises\";\n 278| \n 279| const OPENROUTER_KEY = process.env.OPENROUTER_API_KEY;\n 280| const API_URL = process.env.API_URL;\n 281| const MODEL = process.env.MODEL;\n 282| \n 283| // ANSI colors\n 284| const RESET = \"\\x1b[0m\";\n 285| const BOLD = \"\\x1b[1m\";\n 286| const DIM = \"\\x1b[2m\";\n 287| const BLUE = \"\\x1b[34m\";\n 288| const CYAN = \"\\x1b[36m\";\n 289| const GREEN = \"\\x1b[32m\";\n 290| const YELLOW = \"\\x1b[33m\";\n 291| const RED = \"\\x1b[31m\";\n 292| \n 293| function renderMarkdown(text: string): string {\n 294|     return text.replace(/\\*\\*(.+?)\\*\\*/g, `${BOLD}$1${RESET}`);\n 295| }\n 296| \n 297| function separator() {\n 298|     return `${DIM}${\"─\".repeat(Math.min(process.stdout.columns || 80, 80))}${RESET}`;\n 299| }\n 300| \n 301| \n 302| const stats = {\n 303|     requests: 0,\n 304|     tools: {} as Record<string, number>,\n 305|     logs: [] as string[]\n 306| };\n 307| \n 308| async function callApi(messages: any[], systemPrompt: string) {\n 309|     stats.requests++;\n 310|     const headers: Record<string, string> = {\n 311|         \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n 312|         \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${process.env.OPENROUTER_KEY || process.env.OPENROUTER_API_KEY || \"\"}`,\n 313|     };\n 314| \n 315|     let url = API_URL;\n 316|     if (!url) throw new Error(\"API_URL is undefined\");\n 317| \n 318|     if (!url.endsWith(\"/chat/completions\")) {\n 319|         url = url.endsWith(\"/\") ? `${url}chat/completions` : `${url}/chat/completions`;\n 320|     }\n 321| \n 322|     const tools = makeSchema().map(tool => ({\n 323|         type: \"function\",\n 324|         function: {\n 325|             name: tool.name,\n 326|             description: tool.description,\n 327|             parameters: tool.input_schema\n 328|         }\n 329|     }));\n 330| \n 331|     // Convert internal message format to OpenAI format\n 332|     const convertedMessages: any[] = [\n 333|         { role: \"system\", content: systemPrompt },\n 334|     ];\n 335| \n 336|     for (const msg of messages) {\n 337|         if (msg.role === \"user\" && Array.isArray(msg.content) && msg.content[0]?.type === \"tool_result\") {\n 338|             for (const res of msg.content) {\n 339|                 convertedMessages.push({\n 340|                     role: \"tool\",\n 341|                     tool_call_id: res.tool_use_id,\n 342|                     content: res.content\n 343|                 });\n 344|             }\n 345|         } else if (msg.role === \"assistant\" && Array.isArray(msg.content)) {\n 346|             const textParts = msg.content.filter((c: any) => c.type === \"text\").map((c: any) => c.text).join(\"\\n\");\n 347|             const toolCalls = msg.content.filter((c: any) => c.type === \"tool_use\").map((c: any) => ({\n 348|                 id: c.id,\n 349|                 type: \"function\",\n 350|                 function: {\n 351|                     name: c.name,\n 352|                     arguments: JSON.stringify(c.input)\n 353|                 }\n 354|             }));\n 355| \n 356|             const asstMsg: any = { role: \"assistant\" };\n 357|             if (textParts) asstMsg.content = textParts;\n 358|             if (toolCalls.length > 0) asstMsg.tool_calls = toolCalls;\n 359|             convertedMessages.push(asstMsg);\n 360|         } else {\n 361|             convertedMessages.push({ role: msg.role, content: typeof msg.content === 'string' ? msg.content : JSON.stringify(msg.content) });\n 362|         }\n 363|     }\n 364| \n 365|     const body = {\n 366|         model: MODEL,\n 367|         messages: convertedMessages,\n 368|         tools,\n 369|     };\n 370| \n 371|     await appendFile(\"api_responses.log\", `[Request] ${new Date().toISOString()}\\n${JSON.stringify(body)}\\n\\n`);\n 372| \n 373|     const controller = new AbortController();\n 374|     const timeout = setTimeout(() => controller.abort(), 60000);\n 375| \n 376|     try {\n 377|         const response = await fetch(url, {\n 378|             method: \"POST\",\n 379|             headers,\n 380|             body: JSON.stringify(body),\n 381|             signal: controller.signal\n 382|         });\n 383| \n 384|         if (!response.ok) {\n 385|             throw new Error(`API Error: ${response.status} ${response.statusText} - ${await response.text()}`);\n 386|         }\n 387| \n 388|         const data = await response.json();\n 389|         await appendFile(\"api_responses.log\", `[Response] ${new Date().toISOString()}\\n${JSON.stringify(data)}\\n\\n---\\n\\n`);\n 390| \n 391|         // Convert OpenAI response to internal format\n 392|         const choice = data.choices[0];\n 393|         const msg = choice.message;\n 394|         const content: any[] = [];\n 395| \n 396|         if (msg.content) {\n 397|             content.push({ type: \"text\", text: msg.content });\n 398|         }\n 399|         if (msg.tool_calls) {\n 400|             for (const call of msg.tool_calls) {\n 401|                 content.push({\n 402|                     type: \"tool_use\",\n 403|                     id: call.id,\n 404|                     name: call.function.name,\n 405|                     input: JSON.parse(call.function.arguments)\n 406|                 });\n 407|             }\n 408|         }\n 409|         return { content };\n 410|     } finally {\n 411|         clearTimeout(timeout);\n 412|     }\n 413| }\n 414| \n 415| async function main() {\n 416|     console.log(`${BOLD}nanocode${RESET} | ${DIM}${MODEL} | ${process.cwd()}${RESET}\\n`);\n 417| \n 418|     let messages: any[] = [];\n 419|     const systemPrompt = `Concise coding assistant. cwd: ${process.cwd()}`;\n 420|     // Helper for reading input\n 421|     console.log(separator());\n 422| \n 423|     while (true) {\n 424|         process.stdout.write(`${BOLD}${BLUE}❯${RESET} `);\n 425|         // prompt() is a global in Bun (synchronous)\n 426|         const userInput = prompt(\"\");\n 427|         console.log(separator());\n 428| \n 429|         if (!userInput) continue;\n 430| \n 431|         const input = userInput.trim();\n 432| \n 433|         // Log user input\n 434|         const userSummary = `${new Date().toISOString()} | USER | ${input}`;\n 435|         stats.logs.push(userSummary);\n 436|         await appendFile(\"actions.log\", userSummary + \"\\n\");\n 437| \n 438|         if ([\"/q\", \"exit\"].includes(input)) {\n 439|             break;\n 440|         }\n 441| \n 442|         if (input.startsWith(\"/stats\")) {\n 443|             const parts = input.split(\" \");\n 444|             const path = parts[1];\n 445|             const content = [\n 446|                 `Total Requests: ${stats.requests}`,\n 447|                 `Tool Usage:`,\n 448|                 ...Object.entries(stats.tools).map(([name, count]) => `  - ${name}: ${count}`),\n 449|                 `Logs:`,\n 450|                 ...stats.logs\n 451|             ].join(\"\\n\");\n 452| \n 453|             if (path) {\n 454|                 await Bun.write(path, content);\n 455|                 console.log(`${GREEN}⏺ Stats saved to ${path}${RESET}`);\n 456|             } else {\n 457|                 console.log(`${CYAN}Stats:${RESET}\\n${content}`);\n 458|             }\n 459|             continue;\n 460|         }\n 461| \n 462|         if (input === \"/c\") {\n 463|             messages = [];\n 464|             console.log(`${GREEN}⏺ Cleared conversation${RESET}`);\n 465|             continue;\n 466|         }\n 467| \n 468|         messages.push({ role: \"user\", content: input });\n 469|         // console.error(`DEBUG: Processing input: \"${input}\"`);\n 470| \n 471|         try {\n 472|             // Agentic loop\n 473|             while (true) {\n 474|                 // console.error(\"DEBUG: Calling API...\");\n 475|                 const response: any = await callApi(messages, systemPrompt);\n 476|                 // console.error(\"DEBUG: API Response received\");\n 477| \n 478|                 const contentBlocks = response.content || [];\n 479|                 const toolResults: any[] = [];\n 480| \n 481|                 for (const block of contentBlocks) {\n 482|                     if (block.type === \"text\") {\n 483|                         console.log(`\\n${CYAN}⏺${RESET} ${renderMarkdown(block.text)}`);\n 484|                         // Log assistant text\n 485|                         const asstSummary = `${new Date().toISOString()} | ASSISTANT | ${block.text.replace(/\\n/g, \"\\\\n\")}`;\n 486|                         stats.logs.push(asstSummary);\n 487|                         await appendFile(\"actions.log\", asstSummary + \"\\n\");\n 488|                     }\n 489| \n 490|                     if (block.type === \"tool_use\") {\n 491|                         const toolName = block.name;\n 492|                         const toolArgs = block.input;\n 493|                         const argPreview = JSON.stringify(Object.values(toolArgs)[0] || \"\").slice(0, 50);\n 494| \n 495|                         stats.tools[toolName] = (stats.tools[toolName] || 0) + 1;\n 496| \n 497|                         console.log(`\\n${GREEN}⏺ ${toolName.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + toolName.slice(1)}${RESET}(${DIM}${argPreview}${RESET})`);\n 498|                         // console.error(`DEBUG: Running tool ${toolName}...`);\n 499| \n 500|                         let result;\n 501|                         try {\n 502|                             result = await runTool(toolName, toolArgs);\n 503|                         } catch (err: any) {\n 504|                             result = `error: ${err.message}`;\n 505|                         }\n 506| \n 507|                         // Log action summary\n 508|                         const summary = `${new Date().toISOString()} | ${toolName} | ${JSON.stringify(toolArgs)} | ${String(result).slice(0, 100).replace(/\\n/g, \"\\\\n\")}`;\n 509|                         stats.logs.push(summary); // Store in memory for /stats\n 510|                         await appendFile(\"actions.log\", summary + \"\\n\");\n 511| \n 512|                         // Formatting result preview\n 513|                         const resultStr = String(result);\n 514|                         const resultLines = resultStr.split(\"\\n\");\n 515|                         let preview = resultLines[0]?.slice(0, 60) || \"\";\n 516|                         if (resultLines.length > 1) {\n 517|                             preview += ` ... +${resultLines.length - 1} lines`;\n 518|                         } else if (resultLines[0]?.length > 60) {\n 519|                             preview += \"...\";\n 520|                         }\n 521|                         console.log(`  ${DIM}⎿  ${preview}${RESET}`);\n 522| \n 523|                         toolResults.push({\n 524|                             type: \"tool_result\",\n 525|                             tool_use_id: block.id,\n 526|                             content: resultStr,\n 527|                         });\n 528|                     }\n 529|                 }\n 530| \n 531|                 messages.push({ role: \"assistant\", content: contentBlocks });\n 532| \n 533|                 if (toolResults.length === 0) {\n 534|                     break;\n 535|                 }\n 536|                 messages.push({ role: \"user\", content: toolResults });\n 537|             }\n 538|         } catch (err: any) {\n 539|             if (err.name === 'AbortError' || err.message === 'Interrupted') break;\n 540|             console.log(`${RED}⏺ Error: ${err.message}${RESET}`);\n 541|             console.error(\"DEBUG Stack:\", err.stack);\n 542|         }\n 543|         console.log();\n 544|     }\n 545| }\n 546| \n 547| if (import.meta.main) {\n 548|     main().catch(console.error);\n 549| }"},{"role":"assistant","content":"Let me also check the package.json and .env files to understand the dependencies and configuration:\n\n","tool_calls":[{"id":"call_1874369085994dd29c11cda2","type":"function","function":{"name":"read","arguments":"{\"path\":\"package.json\"}"}}]},{"role":"tool","tool_call_id":"call_1874369085994dd29c11cda2","content":"   1| {\n   2|   \"dependencies\": {\n   3|     \"zod\": \"^3.21.4\"\n   4|   }\n   5| }"},{"role":"assistant","tool_calls":[{"id":"call_8c40b30951f840df9368cf4a","type":"function","function":{"name":"read","arguments":"{\"path\":\".env\"}"}}]},{"role":"tool","tool_call_id":"call_8c40b30951f840df9368cf4a","content":"   1| OPENROUTER_KEY=\"sk-081adacbc7d6451eaa95cfbcd2385b2d\"\n   2| API_URL=\"https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1\"\n   3| MODEL=\"qwen3-max\""},{"role":"assistant","content":"Based on my analysis of the repository files, here's what this repo does:\n\n## **TinyClaude - An AI-Powered Coding Assistant**\n\nThis repository implements a **local AI coding assistant** that provides agentic capabilities through a command-line interface. It's built with TypeScript and Bun runtime.\n\n### **Core Features:**\n\n1. **File System Operations**: \n   - Read files with line numbering and optional offset/limit\n   - Write files\n   - Edit files by replacing specific strings (with safety checks)\n   - Glob pattern matching for file discovery\n   - Grep functionality for searching across files\n\n2. **System Commands**: \n   - Execute bash commands with 30-second timeout protection\n\n3. **AI Integration**: \n   - Connects to OpenRouter-compatible APIs (currently configured for Alibaba's DashScope/Qwen3)\n   - Uses function calling to let the AI use the available tools\n   - Maintains conversation history with tool usage context\n\n4. **Interactive CLI**: \n   - Real-time chat interface with colored output\n   - Command shortcuts (`/q` to quit, `/c` to clear conversation, `/stats` for usage statistics)\n   - Automatic logging of all interactions to `actions.log` and API responses to `api_responses.log`\n\n### **How It Works:**\n\nThe assistant operates in an **agentic loop**:\n1. User provides a coding task or question\n2. AI analyzes the request and decides which tools to use\n3. Tools execute (file operations, system commands, etc.)\n4. Results are fed back to the AI for further reasoning\n5. Process repeats until the task is complete or user intervention is needed\n\n### **Current Configuration:**\n- Uses **Qwen3-Max** model via Alibaba's DashScope API\n- Designed for concise, coding-focused assistance\n- Includes safety features like timeout protection and edit validation\n\nThis is essentially a **local development assistant** that can help with code navigation, file manipulation, and general programming tasks by combining AI reasoning with direct filesystem access."},{"role":"user","content":"\\stats"},{"role":"assistant","content":"I notice you're asking for stats, but the `\\stats` command is meant to be used within the running nanocode assistant application. Since we're not currently running the interactive CLI, I can't execute that command directly.\n\nHowever, I can check if there are any existing stats logs in the rep